de.tub.data.dao
Class Neo4JStaypointDAO

java.lang.Object
  de.tub.data.dao.Neo4JStaypointDAO
All Implemented Interfaces:
IDao, IStaypointDAO<org.neo4j.graphdb.Node>, Cloneable
public class Neo4JStaypointDAO
extends Object
implements IStaypointDAO<org.neo4j.graphdb.Node>, Cloneable

This class gives the possibility to access a framework cluster. It hides the technology of access so that the programmer does not have to worry about during usage. The Neo4JStaypointDAO class is part of the Data Access Object design pattern. That is why it implements the IStaypointDAO interface with all its methods.
Furthermore it implements the interface Clonable. This makes it possible to clone an instance of Neo4JStaypointDAO and makes this class a part of the Prototype design pattern.

Author:
Sebastian Oelke

Neo4JStaypointDAO

public Neo4JStaypointDAO(Neo4JStaypointDAO stayPointDao)
Copy constructor for use with the Prototype design pattern. If you use clone() this constructor has to be used and all instance variables have to be copied.
Because the Neo4JStaypointDAO class has no instance variables to copy this constructor is equivalent with the standard constructor.

Parameters:
stayPointDao - The Neo4JStaypointDAO which has to be copied.
